cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.CR, cs.CC, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the evolving connectivity of large content provider networks from a topological point of view of the autonomous systems (AS) graph. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper discusses the adoption of IXPs as a convenient method for peering and the diversification of neighbor connectivity. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possible category as the paper briefly mentions traffic shaping becoming increasingly popular. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on complexity theory or algorithms. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a less likely category as the paper does not focus on information theory or coding theory.
